details:
verb
- eliminate from the body
= synonyms: pass
- kill in large numbers
= synonyms: annihilate, extinguish, eradicate, wipe out, decimate, carry off
- terminate, end, or take out
= example: terminate, end, or take out
= synonyms: get rid of, do away with, extinguish
- remove (an unknown variable) from two or more equations
- dismiss from consideration or a contest
= synonyms: reject
- remove from a contest or race
= example: remove from a contest or race
- do away with
= synonyms: get rid of, obviate, abolish, rid of
